LICENSING RATIONALE

Core 1 is architecturally and legally separate from the GPL-3.0 Meshtastic
stack running on Core 0. The two cores communicate at arm's length through
a well-defined IPC protocol (see firmware/shared/ipc/), with no shared
source-level includes or direct function calls crossing the boundary.
This design mirrors the separation between a GPL kernel and non-GPL userspace,
as recognised by the FSF GPL FAQ.
